          <text>
                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>
                                        <date>5 July 1848</date>
                              </p>
                              <p>
                                        <addressee>Revd Mr Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(2)">My Dr Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Accompanying this letter you have the<lb/>
                                        manuscript copy of the Laws for the Government of the<lb/>
                                        Congregation of the Island which is entrusted to your<lb/>
                                        care for printing, we require five hundred copies &amp;
                                        wish<lb/> them printed in pamphlet form neatly done up &amp;
                                        executed<lb/> with dispatch. I have assured my colleagues
                                        that you<lb/> would execute the order for a moderate price.
                                        We could have<lb/> them done for $50 here this we considered
                                        too much—you will<lb/> please send them by 2 opportunities
                                        each with 250 copies.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">The slaves in the <placeName>Danish
                                                  Colonies</placeName> were liberated<lb/> on the
                                                  <date>3d Jun</date> at <placeName>St.
                                                  Croix</placeName>, &amp; yesterday here &amp;
                                                  <placeName>St Johns</placeName>, the
                                        Govern-<lb/>ment at <placeName>St Croix</placeName> was
                                        faced by a demonstration of 7000 slaves<lb/> the opposing
                                        face very inadequate, it was unexpected by the<lb/>
                                        Government &amp; Inhabitants &amp; appeared an organized
                                        affair, some<lb/> excesses were committed there the
                                        particulars of which we have<lb/> not received. I am happy
                                        to state that it went off well<lb/> here, the liberated only
                                        singing through the streets <date>8 July</date> the<lb/>
                                        excesses in <placeName>St Croix</placeName> are lamentable,
                                        after the people were freed they<lb/> became lawless,
                                        destroying property in every way setting fire &amp;<lb/>
                                        what could not be destroyed in this way, they did so
                                        wantonly<lb/> by knocking in the heads of the Puncheons of
                                        Rum &amp; molasses<lb/> selling the <add>?</add> of sugar
                                        over precipices thereby <add>?</add> them &amp;<lb/> sending
                                        the sugar to the winds pulling down Houses &amp;c</p>
                              <p rend="indent(8)">I am D Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <persName role="author">A. Wolff</persName>
                              </p>
                    </body>
